# UI composition patterns

Most UI components fit one of these six patterns. Copy-adapt before inventing.

## 1. Measurer component

All four measurers ([LengthMeasurer](src/components/bim/LengthMeasurer.tsx), [AreaMeasurer](src/components/bim/AreaMeasurer.tsx), [VolumeMeasurer](src/components/bim/VolumeMeasurer.tsx), [AngleMeasurer](src/components/bim/AngleMeasurer.tsx)) follow the same shape:

```tsx
export const FooMeasurer = () => {
  const [measurer, mutateMeasurer] = useBimComponent(BimComponent.FooMeasurer);
  const visible = measurer?.visible ?? false;

  return (
    <section className="w-48 bim-component-container">
      <ul className="bim-component-guide"><li>Double click to ...</li></ul>
      <div className="justify-start! gap-2! *:cursor-pointer">
        <input
          type="checkbox"
          checked={visible}
          onChange={e => mutateMeasurer(x => { x.visible = e.target.checked })}
        />
        <label>Measurement visible</label>
      </div>
      <button className="btn-gray" onClick={() => measurer?.list.clear()}>Delete All</button>
    </section>
  );
};
```

## 2. Toolbar button wrapper

For anything that toggles a BIM component from the bottom toolbar, wrap [BottomToolbarButton](src/components/ui/BottomToolbar/ToggleButtons/index.tsx#L20) (defined alongside the re-exports in `ToggleButtons/index.tsx`) — it owns enable/disable, chevron, and click-outside. Don't re-implement:

```tsx
export const FooMeasurerButton = () => (
  <BottomToolbarButton
    componentKey={BimComponent.FooMeasurer}
    componentNode={<FooMeasurer />}
    tooltipMessage="Foo measurement"
    icon={<IconFoo />}
  />
);
```

Camera/orientation-style dropdowns use the accordion variants in [BottomToolbar/AccordionButtons/](src/components/ui/BottomToolbar/AccordionButtons/).

## 3. Nav-rail panel wrapper

Every left-drawer panel (`ModelsPanel`, `ClassifierPanel`, `ModelInspectorPanel`, `ViewsPanel`, `SettingsPanel` in [src/components/ui/NavigationRailDrawer/panels/](src/components/ui/NavigationRailDrawer/panels/)) is:

```tsx
<>
  <PanelHeader title="Foo" />
  <section className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto">
    <div className="nav-rail-drawer-panel">
      <FooContent />
    </div>
  </section>
</>
```

## 4. BUI mount (for @thatopen/ui web components)

Complex tables/charts (`Classifier`, `ItemInspector`, `ModelInspector`, `ModelAttributes`, `TwoDViews`) embed `@thatopen/ui` web components via dynamic import:

```tsx
export const Foo = () => {
  const containerRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
  const [someDep] = useBimComponent(BimComponent.SomeDep);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!someDep) return;
    const container = containerRef.current;
    let panel: HTMLElement | null = null;

    (async () => {
      const BUI = await import("@thatopen/ui");
      panel = BUI.Component.create(() => BUI.html`<bim-panel>...</bim-panel>`);
      if (container) {
        container.innerHTML = "";
        container.appendChild(panel);
      }
    })();

    return () => {
      if (panel && container?.contains(panel)) container.removeChild(panel);
    };
  }, [someDep]);

  return <div ref={containerRef} />;
};
```

ShadowDOM styling: `panel.shadowRoot?.querySelector(...)`. BUI init happens once via `BimExtensions.initBUI()` called from `BimManager`.

## 5. Draggable resize handle

[NavigationRailDrawer](src/components/ui/NavigationRailDrawer/NavigationRailDrawer.tsx) and [RightDrawer](src/components/ui/RightDrawer.tsx) both use:

```tsx
const [isResizing, setIsResizing] = useState(false);

useEffect(() => {
  if (!isResizing) return;

  document.body.style.userSelect = "none";
  document.body.style.cursor = "col-resize";
  const ac = new AbortController();

  document.addEventListener("mousemove", e => {
    e.preventDefault();
    setWidth(clamp(/* compute */, min, max));
  }, { signal: ac.signal });

  document.addEventListener("mouseup", () => {
    setIsResizing(false);
    document.body.style.userSelect = "";
    document.body.style.cursor = "";
  }, { signal: ac.signal });

  return () => ac.abort();
}, [isResizing]);
```

`AbortController` is the standard cleanup mechanism throughout this codebase — prefer it over named handler + `removeEventListener`.

## 6. Data-attribute styling

State-driven styling uses `data-*` attributes matched by CSS in [src/app/globals.css](src/app/globals.css), not conditional class strings:

```tsx
<button data-active={isActive} className="button-toolbar-button">…</button>
```

```css
.button-toolbar-button[data-active="true"] { /* … */ }
```

Conventions: `data-active`, `data-open`, `data-enabled`, `data-disabled`, `data-position`. New conditional styling should join this system rather than inline `clsx`/`cn` chains.

## Small conventions

- **Icons**: `@radix-ui/react-icons` for stock; inline SVG components in [src/components/ui/icons/](src/components/ui/icons/) for custom (`IconCamera`, `IconCompass`, `IconPaintRoller`, `IconSitemap`). No icon fonts.
- **Tooltip**: always via `<WithTooltip position="top|bottom" message="…">` ([WithTooltip.tsx](src/components/ui/WithTooltip.tsx)) — don't hand-roll.
- **MUI surface**: only `Switch` via [SwitchButton](src/components/ui/buttons/SwitchButton.tsx). Don't introduce additional MUI components without a concrete reason — Tailwind + native HTML is the default.
- **Component exports**: `export const Foo = () => { ... }` (see [follow-user-scope.mdc](.cursor/rules/follow-user-scope.mdc)).
- **All UI is client-side**: only [src/app/layout.tsx](src/app/layout.tsx) is a server component. Every new UI file is implicitly `"use client"` via the tree.
